INSERT INTO `job_appliedjobs` VALUES (765, '2010-08-03', 128, 2783, 'Yes, five and half years now on a project worth BWP15 million', 'I would start by understanding the reasons why the team doesn''t want to work. I will proceed to find a resolution to any issues that may surface as related to the team''s refusal, if there are. Assertively and professionally, I will explain to the team the reasons clearly why that something has to be done. Through balanced skills of good leadership, and with well calculated firmness (for demonstration of seriousness) and fairness of a good manager, I will discuss my objectives until I win the support of the members. After focusing the members to the task, I will seek their contributions on how the task can be tackled and objectively consider them for adoption if they have merit. This way, I will ensure that the members feel a sense of ownership of whatever needs to be undertaken.Once everyone is focused, I will make clear my expectations and what I will evaluate on. I will offer myself support on a continuous basis and also ensure that the team really feels that I identify with them in all aspects of the task. ', '- I am highly skilled and experienced in Plant and equipment maintenance.\r\n- I posses high diagnostic and trouble shooting skills in mechanical, electromechanical, electropneumatics and hydraulic fields.\r\n- I have excellent man-management skills and have inert abilities to motivate people to tasks on sustainable basis\r\n- I have excellent organisational, analytical and communication skills.\r\n- From my General Management experiences, I have the abilities in Finance management, accounts and use of financial statements for sound decision making purposes and other. \r\n- I am a good leader with a traceable track record ', '- I enjoy leadership the most. I think this is because I value and draw great joy in seeing subordinates reach their full potential professionally simply through my leadership style. It gives me great pleasure to see people rally behind me because they voluntarily share my vision in whatever I undertake to do.\r\n- I also enjoy duties related to the efficient and effective utilisation of resources, be it time, finance, people, raw material or back up spares. I operate with a winning mentality and I suppose I enjoy this because I reckon efficient resource utilisation is one of the most important critical success factors of any organisation.', 'I know Meatco to be a giant in the meat processing and exporting sector of the region. With the stringent export conditions it has to endure, this gives me a perfect environment to pursue my career in the food industry. I have had such an experience before, with especially Bonnezim. This industry presents to me the exact challenges that I would like to undertake once again.  ', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0);
