INSERT INTO `job_appliedjobs` VALUES (811, '2010-08-09', 131, 2398, 'First of all I do not believe that there are difficult customers. Customers only become difficult if they do not receive the service we promise them. I see this opportunity to improve on our customer service. \r\nSolving the customers’ problem/concern I will do the following:  \r\n&#61482;	Show RESPECT, "No matter what, I will respect the customer." \r\n&#61482;	Empathized, Listen.  \r\n&#61482;	Get the information and avoid blame.  Acknowledge and apologize for it.\r\n&#61482;	Resolve the problem.\r\nIt is critical to leave the irate customer with the understanding that my goal is to resolve the problem. I will find out what I can do for this customer and do it. Then I follow up with the customer when I said I would. Even if I you don''t have all the information I need, I will call when I  said I would and at least let him know what I''ve done, what I am  working on and what my  next step will be. I will let the customer know that he and his business are important to me, that I understand his frustration. \r\n', 'I have excellent preparatory abilities with using Power Point presentations .Advanced proficiency levels in Microsoft office applications including Access, Excel, and Outlook Express. Notepad and Word.', 'The key to improving service is motivated employees. Ensure that all the individuals in your business not only know what you expect of them, but also have a vested interest in the business. Staff must know why you want to keep customers happy, how to do it. As the team leader of the investment department I am responsible for: \r\n&#61656;	Satisfied customers internal and external\r\n&#61656;	Retention\r\n&#61656;	Service excellence\r\nCustomers are the primary reason for being in business  \r\n&#61602;	Empowerment  -On the spot-decision how to deal with those problems not included in the written procedures \r\n&#61602;	Everyone''s Business –  trained staff to deal with customer complaints  \r\n', 'One of my responsibilities as the team leader for the investment department was to develop a competitive sales strategy that anticipates competitor actions and places my company as the best in the market to meet customer objectives.  I was always on top of the interest rates and the different products our competitors were offering. Having the advantages of the tax free benefit, excellent service delivery, I could easily make a sale with a potential investor. AND build a long lasting relationship. My approached was sometimes visiting the clients, and by means of presentations at various trade show, schools etc. ', 'Old Mutual has improved its employee ratings on several important\r\ndimensions including job satisfaction, diversity, and training\r\nand development. In fact, job satisfaction has emerged as the\r\ntop-scoring dimension for the last five years, which implies that\r\nOld Mutual employees on the whole are feeling challenged and\r\nsatisfied in their jobs. Eighty-seven percent of Old Mutual’s clients\r\nsurveyed in 2005 indicated they were satisfied with the service\r\nthey had received and 57% of clients were delighted by the\r\nservice they had received, ten points above the industry average of 47%. I would love to be part of this team.\r\n', '', 100, 0, 50, 0, 5, 1, 0);
