INSERT INTO `job_appliedjobs` VALUES (950, '2010-08-20', 131, 941, 'I worked with business people from various ethnic groups and cultures in the occupational wages survey, this has helped me to understand the word customer care to a whole new level.', 'I am also studying towards my 23BECO degree at the Polytechnic of Namibia, meaning that this position will help me gain experience and help your organization grow at the same time.   ', 'When I was working for the Min of labour and social welfare, we were faced with communication problems as some customers could not communicate properly with us and others were really offensive but I have learned that patience and understanding is very important in achieving a customer''s trust.   ', 'When I was in high school,I worked at OK foods as a cashier in Katima for a year, It was challenging but with training and ample time to learn, I became an expert. I am aware that customer care is very challenging but with ample resources and guidance, I can work at the best of my abilities ', 'Old Mutual Namibia is a well recognized financial company and I have always wanted to work in an environment where I can exercise my skills and learn at the same time.', 'Thelma Lupalezwi\r\nP O Box 40829\r\nAusspannplatz\r\nWindhoek\r\nNamibia\r\n\r\nOld Mutual Namibia\r\nPostal Address:\r\nPO Box 165 \r\nWindhoek \r\nNamibia\r\n\r\nRE:  APPLICATION FOR THE SALES ADVISOR POSITION	\r\n\r\nI am hereby applying for the advertised post of SALES ADVISOR in your organization. I believe that I posses the required qualities and skills which will make me an impact player in your organization while aiming at the same time to make a difference in my nation. I am currently studying towards my degree in Economics at the polytechnic of Namibia. I will be glad if you could grant me an interview to come and explain myself in detail. In case of any open vacancies in your company, I am available for any banking or administrative job.\r\n\r\nAttached are my Curricul