INSERT INTO `job_appliedjobs` VALUES (2281, '2011-04-18', 308, 6320, '', '', '', '', '', '                                                                                                                                 	MorreenKasume\r\n	P.O Box 98057\r\n	Windhoek, Namibia\r\n                                                                                                                                   1 8 April 2011       \r\nTO: Deep Catch Trading\r\n \r\n\r\nDear Sir/Madam\r\n\r\nVacancy applying for: Junior Assistant Buyer\r\n\r\nThe position advertised on the Nam Recruit website on the 18/04/11 caught my attention as I believe this position can serve as a great learning opportunity for me and broaden my understanding on a lot of issues.\r\n\r\nI am currently rewriting my grade 12 but I  have over six years experience as a receptionist which I acquired working for organizations called Catholic Aids Action and INFOSA (a Marketing Information and Advisory Services Organization). There I was responsible for operation the switchboard by receiving phone calls and directing them to the rightful individuals, taking and relaying messages, receiving hand delivered mail from outside, sign out, sort and distributes to the right persons, typing documents, dealing with queries form the public and customers and arranging for couriers to collect outgoing mail.\r\n \r\nI also have one and a half years worth of experience working as a personal assistant which I acquired working for a consultancy organization called Face It Training Services.\r\nI worked closely with the director, arrange her office dairy and travel itineraries, assisting with scheduling hosting of functions, maintain a good filling system, screening her calls, inquiries and requests and handling them when appropriate. I also reviewed incoming mail, faxes and letters and produced documents, briefing papers, reports and presentations, and carrying out background research and presenting the findings into subjects the director was dealing with. As a PA I also maintained the director’s calendar that included functions, meetings, travel, events etc, and I also organized and attended meetings and ensured the director was well prepared for them.\r\nI stood in for the director in her absence, made decisions and delegated work to others.\r\n\r\nAmong my particular strengths are my organizational and planning skills. I have developed a number of processes to manage my many work tasks and make sure I meet the demand of a fast – paced work environment.\r\n My strong communication skills and energetic, humble personality ensure a first rate customer service to both clients and colleagues. I thoroughly enjoy dealing with a wide variety of people and take pride in my work.\r\n\r\nI am confident that I have the oomph to contribute to and strengthen your team because of determination, my willingness to learn and my personality.\r\nI would appreciate the opportunity to discuss my abilities in more depth and am available for an interview at your earliest convenience.\r\nI have attached my CV along with all the necessary documents, which will elaborate more on my duties.\r\n\r\n\r\nYours in anticipation\r\n\r\n…………………\r\nMorreen Kasume\r\n', 66.67, 0, 33.34, 0, 0, 0, 0);
