INSERT INTO `job_appliedjobs` VALUES (1438, '2010-10-31', 189, 1665, '', '', '', '', '', 'Cover Letter for the Position of\r\nHuman Resources Manager\r\nDear Ms/Sir\r\n\r\nI’d like to bring my success as a senior-level practitioner and trainer to Harare in the HRM/ETM/IR position you are currently advertising.\r\n\r\nI am a professional IR consultant, trainer, facilitator, consultant, and educator with 10+ years of experience in Performance and Training that is solidly grounded in creating a positive learning environment by building a high degree of rapport with participants, thus facilitating lasting change. \r\n\r\nI have successfully conceptualized, developed, and implemented innovative training programs that responded quickly to emerging needs and trends. I consistently ensure acquisition and enhancement of skills and competencies, implement performance support activities, function as the single point of contact for all of the site’s training and development needs – and much more.\r\n\r\nI am known for my enthusiastic and engaging training style. I interact well with everyone from front-line workers to top executives, and I have the leadership skills to inspire and motivate. My diverse and broad-based background has sharpened my organizational and analytical skills.\r\n\r\nAs a strong interpersonal communicator, I have consistently built rapport in my training programs. My goal is simple; I invite people into the heart of transformation by creating a connection through their passion, their purpose, and their unlimited potential. I am convinced that Harare Training, Learning and Performance Solutions  could benefit from my ability to coax the best out of people.\r\n\r\nI’m no stranger to ETD, having conducted a cultural profile on manufacturing, building and services company’s nationwide, thus providing leaders with feedback and data to help them to clarify the direction for strategic planning. \r\n\r\nTo supplement my profile For the past ten year, I am involved in technical control and organization of human capital training technical, soft and HETD, VETD, FETD, strategic planning, policies, frameworks for managing human resources performance and implementation. Coupled with this I was a pioneer in the development of Human Resource blended with operational excellence.\r\n\r\nMy knowledge and experience in this regard is immaculate and even though my job descriptions seem simple, I usually influenced and convinced much senior office bearers than myself, had the respect  of much senior academic staff. I usually built strategies within strategies and thus had huge success within the consultancies, projects and Multi-Nationals that I worked for. \r\n\r\nI was an extremely strict practitioner and consultant trainer, but a very open facilitator and part-time lecturer in Human Resources and Human Resource Management but this is not a role I benchmark myself against, rather my results that I achieved, which are: \r\n\r\n1.	Complete contractual adherence policy drafting, implementation and conforming \r\n2.	Zero fines on AA reports, \r\n3.	Complete growth in training areas with a position ROI , \r\n4.	Complete quality adherence to human resource process, \r\n5.	Little or successful chaired industrial action, but completed trained supervisors,\r\n6.	Complete union support, and flowing into a more partnership relationship, \r\n7.	Promoter and champion of cultural, diversity development, and communicator,\r\n8.	Impassionate of job roles and tasks, internal and external customer of HR\r\n9.	Performance orientated but still enjoying life, management style, etc\r\n10.	Complete cost and financial adherence and accountability to budget and cost centre\r\n11.	OEE growth of 30%plus, training initiatives of 200% growth.\r\n12.	Zero drop-out of training events\r\n\r\nI hope this is favor, \r\n\r\nSincerely,\r\nMarius Frederick Johannes\r\n0814633120\r\nPERFORMANCE • ACCOUNTABILITY\r\n', 33.33, 0, 16.66, 0, 0, 0, 0);
